dance performance rodin and the dancing body events at stanford dance performance rodin and the dancing body facebook twitter email print add to calendar in conjunction with the exhibition rodin and america muriel maffre lecturer in the dance division of the drama department and former principal dancer with the san francisco ballet teaches a fall course for stanford students to explore the intersection between rodin and dance rodin's friendship with local dance artist isadora duncan is the starting point for this engaging installation during which students will move through the museum's auditorium with their dancing bodies providing visitors with a unique perspective on a significant aspect of rodin's work for the first time on campus dance artist and lines contemporary ballet director alonzo king will join maffre and her students for a series of open rehearsals during these sessions museum visitors are welcome to observe and to sketch materials provided a final performance by the students will be held in roble gym in early december this collaboration is supported in part by the joan and john jay corley fund for performance when wednesday oct 12 2011 2 15 pm wednesday oct 19 2011 2 15 pm wednesday oct 26 2011 2 15 pm thursday nov 3 2011 6 00 pm thursday nov 10 2011 6 00 pm thursday dec 1 2011 6 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance international dance arts contact 723 3469 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday permalink http events stanford edu events 285 28579 more info last modified november 9 2011
